Japan’s Security Transactions for September: Summary

-- B y   M i n h   B u i
-- 
2011-10-10T23:52:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/japan-s-security-transactions-for-september-summary-table-.html
Japanese investors were 
net buyers of foreign bonds in September according to
figures based on reports from designated major investors 
released by the Ministry of Finance in  Tokyo .  Japanese investors’ net purchases of overseas bonds 
totaled 3111.3 billion yen, while purchases of stocks
were 320.3 billion yen.  The following table shows Japanese investment in
overseas securities, and investment in Japanese securities 
from abroad. A negative sign means net sales, while a
positive number indicates net purchases.  Note 1: Billions of yen.
Note 2: Total net flow are net inflows into  Japan . 
Figures before January 2005 does not include short term securities.
Note 3: Starting from January 2005, portfolio investments are classified
based on the residence of issuers of securities, from the previous securities’
currency of denomination base.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Minh Bui in Tokyo at   mbui@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  